# Karpathy-guidelines

Use these principles when writing, reviewing, or refactoring code in this workspace:

- Think before coding: state assumptions and surface ambiguity.
- Prefer simplicity over over-engineering.
- Make surgical changes and avoid unrelated refactors.
- Define success criteria and verify the result before claiming completion.

For this repository, keep changes scoped to the current service or feature and prefer small, testable increments.
